			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	A few things off the top of my head that I never brought up in that post:<br />
<br />
1.  Blockading as an option only usable in war.<br />
2.  Fleets can't leave for war when their planets are being blockaded.  This would only come into play if blockading was made to be a more-than-one-turn action, which I think realistically and for balancing issues it should be.<br />
3.  Obviously not ALL these changes could be implimented at once; I truly believe that even one of these changes would help a great deal though.  Blockading is, in my opinion, - and a lot of the other gamers' opinions I'm sure - the #1 priority on the AS to do list.  If some of this takes a lot of rewriting a simple fix that would probably take very little work would be either GREATLY decrease the range in which you can blockade, or make it only performable in war circumstances.  I honestly believe that taking blockading out of the game entirely is better than leaving it in under these circumstances.  Hope someone gets on it!  (I know I post a lot of suggestions, please don't misinterpret this as whining, being angry at the AS team, or taking them for granted.  I still believe AS is a great game, and appreciate all the work that's gone into it.)<br />
<br />
-Slayer			   <P align=right></P>
