			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Slayer's ideas rock. Blockading now is absolutely pointless except to gain commander experience. And definitely not the most valiant way to do so either.<br />
<br />
A blockade is to station a large number of ships around a planet (or cluster, according to one of Slayer's suggestions) to stop all physical traffic to and from the planet. A blockading fleet won't come, wipe out defences, and then just leave immediately. That's called a massacre, not a Blockade.<br />
<br />
Anyway, if the devs have no intention of changing the game mechanics of the &quot;blockade&quot;, at least use a more apt word for it. Like &quot;Life-Target Practice&quot; or something. (Forgive the sarcasm. I couldn't help it.) :P<br />
<br />
BTW, please take care of the (sometimes dumb) newbies. Now its a rather harsh punishment for building too many destroyers early on. It's really frustrating to try to build defences, form your defence plan, etc, then be blockaded and totally destroyed by a single HBH doom fleet. And to add insult to injury, the home side didn't even fire a single shot.<br />
<br />
Lastly, this is a suggestion board, not a complaint board or a flaming board. I've seen that happen a few times already. I hope everyone realises the reason for the existence of this forum.<p><br>.			   <P align=right></P>
